  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with atypical symptoms of objectified gastroesophageal reflux disease will be
      treated by full-thickness gastroplication and the effect of this intervention will be
      measured by questionnaires and clinical diagnostics (for example pH/MII).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
